text.section:
The Department of Natural Resources shall establish the program to:
encourage the preservation or development of land for productive woodland purposes;
increase the income of persons in the State from the sale of timber;
prevent flooding of land and the loss of the State's soil;
provide wooded areas for the use and enjoyment of all individuals in the State; and
promote the welfare and assets of the State.

section.section:
Woodland shall be reassessed when:
an agreement ends and is not renewed as provided in subsection (f)(2) of this section;
timber is harvested, unless harvested according to the plan approved by the Department of Natural Resources;
land subject to an agreement is conveyed to a new owner except as provided in subsection (g) of this section; or
an agreement is ended by the Department of Natural Resources at the request of the owner or because the owner has not complied with the agreement.
